        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 11:49AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 1148 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 11 miles east of Deer Lodge to near Butte.
Movement was northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Helena, Boulder, Basin, Wickes, Rimini, Spring Meadow Lake State
Park, Elk Park, Corbin, and Jefferson City.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
